ZH: 我收到了一个红包作为生日礼物。
EN: I received a red envelope as a birthday gift.

ZH: 每年春节我都会收到很多红包。
EN: I receive a lot of red envelopes every Chinese New Year.

ZH: 她生日那天给了我一个红包。
EN: She gave me a red envelope on my birthday.

ZH: 我把压岁钱放在了红包里。
EN: I put the lucky money in the red envelope.

ZH: 在中国，红包是传统的礼物。
EN: Red envelopes are a traditional gift in China.

ZH: 春节时，孩子们都期待着领取红包。
EN: Children look forward to receiving red envelopes during Chinese New Year.

ZH: 我喜欢听到红包里的钱币叮当作响的声音。
EN: I like to hear the coins jingling inside the red envelope.

ZH: 这是一个装有红包的信封。
EN: This is an envelope containing a red packet.

ZH: 我们家每年春节给长辈发放红包。
EN: In our family, we give red envelopes to our elders every Chinese New Year.

ZH: 我中了彩票，决定把一部分奖金放进红包里。
EN: I won the lottery and decided to put a portion of the prize money into red envelopes.

ZH: 小朋友们都兴高采烈地接受大人们给的红包。
EN: Kids happily receive red envelopes from adults.

ZH: 我把压岁钱放在红包里，准备下周给孩子们。
EN: I put lucky money in red envelopes, ready to give them to the children next week.

ZH: 发红包是一种尊敬和祝福的表达。
EN: Giving red envelopes is a way to show respect and blessing.

ZH: 我们公司春节发放了红包给所有员工。
EN: Our company distributed red envelopes to all employees during Chinese New Year.

ZH: 我们赢了比赛，队长给了每个队员一个红包。
EN: We won the game, and the captain gave each team member a red envelope.

ZH: 在中国人的婚礼上，亲戚朋友会纷纷送上红包祝福。
EN: At Chinese weddings, relatives and friends often give red envelopes as blessings.

ZH: 我的新年愿望是多收到一些红包。
EN: My New Year wish is to receive more red envelopes.

ZH: 这个紧急状况让我不得不打开了那份装有红包的信封。
EN: The emergency situation forced me to open the envelope containing the red packet.

ZH: 我每次生日都期待着亲戚们给我红包。
EN: I look forward to receiving red envelopes from relatives on my birthday every year.

ZH: 我把红包里的压岁钱都花在了买新年礼物上。
EN: I spent all the lucky money from the red envelope on buying New Year gifts.
